Commit Message: Add utilities to summarize benchmark results
Move request stats to stats module
Allow to set HTTP headers for requests
Append extra headers to every request during benchmark

Use uvloop event loop

It increases performance by ~20%
Allow to set proxy via cli args
Fix main entry point to be compatible with setup scripts
Add travis CI build status badge

Upgrade aiohttp

Previous version had some bugs with HTTPS over proxy.

Use multiple processes to run tests

This allows to scale over CPU cores.
Use single progress output for all worker processes

Create new event loop if none is specified

In python 3.6 one cannot serialize event loop and pass it to forked process.
This commit fixes that scenario.
Distribute requests evenly among forked worker processes
Add cli argument to set how many process workers to use

Remove typing module from pip requirements

Since python 3.5 it's included in stdlib.

Upgrade coverage and flake8

Last versions would not work properly with python 3.6.
Add makefile target to check types with mypy

Workaround mypy issues

It does not treat partial functions as Callable.
Do static type checking in travis CI
Use standard venv module instead of virtualenv
Make tests work on travis CI
